Spotify is a music streaming platform that allows users to
listen to millions of songs, podcasts, and audio content from artists around the world. Launched in 2008, Spotify offers a seamless listening experience with a free, ad-supported option or a premium subscription without interruptions. Users can create their own playlists, discover new music through smart algorithms, and enjoy high-quality audio on various devices such as phones, computers, and tablets. Additionally, Spotify features Spotify Wrapped, which provides users with a summary of their most-played songs and artists throughout the year. With its vast music library and user-friendly interface, Spotify remains one of the most popular music streaming platforms globally.
